    <string name="settings_hid_pc_mode_title">PC HID mode</string>
    <string name="settings_hid_pc_mode_desc">When on, DeckBridge may send shortcuts and media keys over USB gadget nodes (/dev/hidg*). You still need those nodes (configfs / scripts) and a root grant if SELinux blocks writes. Default is on at first install if privileged shell works.</string>
    <string name="settings_hid_pc_mode_usb_note">The system USB dialog (file transfer, charging only, etc.) does not enable HID; it is separate from the gadget DeckBridge uses. You usually do not need to pick anything there for our HID path—Wi‑Fi debugging does not affect USB HID.</string>
